{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"0b07af8c-9e0a-42fa-8aa8-451a6302962a","content":"For a .NET Web API project, use the `webapi` template:\n\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi -n MyApi\n```\n\n**Authentication options** (via `--auth`):\n\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No authentication (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single-tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows authentication |\n\n**Example with auth:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.onmicrosoft.com\n```\n\nYou can also add JWT Bearer auth manually via `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` for custom identity providers. Want me to scaffold a project with a specific auth option?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4a1eaf23-d37f-4a8e-9dd8-0bba1d296bff","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to search the codebase.","outputTokens":266,"requestId":"C803:2EF340:6FC03FA:77F6BBB:6A03CBB5"},"id":"31cbaf02-dc97-4b64-a0e9-9592bac75f2d","timestamp":"2026-05-13T00:54:20.354Z","parentId":"a170aec1-0b46-41d5-a8e8-0b0c8a70d553"}
